<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-555-308  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 555 308.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Wall Street Journal  August 24 1989 pC9(W) pB2(E) 12 col in.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Toshiba agrees to buy Diasonics's imaging division.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Zachary, G. Pascal.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Toshiba Corp will buy Diasonics Inc's magnetic resonance imagingdivision for $167.5 million, making General Electric Co the onlyUS manufacturer in the medical diagnostic market.andP;  Magneticresonance imaging is used to diagnose problems in the same manneras X-rays, but the new technique provides a better picture of thebody's internal organs and tissues.andP;  Diasonics has been a leaderin the young industry since the company was formed in 1984.andO;Toshiba entered the US magnetic resonance market four years laterwith the creation of Toshiba America Medical Systems Inc.andO;Diasonics makes other diagnostic equipment, but its magneticresonance unit accounted for 40 percent of its revenues.andO;Diasonics' revenues for the qtr ended Jun 30 1989 were $86million.andP;  The company is leaving the magnetic resonance marketbecause of increasing price competition from such diversifiedcompetitors as Toshiba itself.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Toshiba America Medical Systems Inc. (acquisitions and mergers)Diasonics Inc. (divestment).andO;Ticker:    DIA.andO;Topic:     AcquisitionImaging Technology.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>